snippet.title: Lesson 7 - Analyzing Architecture: Structural Decay
snippet.description: In this lesson Mark Richards describes the expectation of an architect to continually analyze architecture to ensure architecture vitality, and defines what it means to detect structural decay in an architecture. Stay tuned each Monday for more lessons in Software Architecture at https://www.developertoarchitect.com/lessons/.
